    <p>
      Most healthcare providers are very busy. They have to have patients in order to cover their fixed costs which are always increasing. However I would wager that the majority of providers did not get into healthcare to see the required daily volume of patients necessary to pay the bills.
    </p>
    <p>
      To the provider there is no other choice; this is how they get paid and rather than go out of business they have to see patients, and as many as they can.
    </p>
    <p>
      Ajax health is going to have an entirely different kind of contract with payers. Rather than getting paid to see patients we will be paid to collect data and provide the tools necessary to leverage that data to effect the health of patients. By partnering with us providers can get off the patient volume treat mill and start to spend their time seeking out the areas where they can do the most good.
      There are too ways to reap the rewards of proactive health management.
    </p>
    <p>
      The first is to work directly with us. Under this arrangement providers will spend their time monitoring groups of patients and identifying areas of improvement. By helping to improve the health of their chosen subset of patients you can effect real change and help your patients to get paid in the process.
    </p>
    <p>
      The second way is to subscribe to our data services. Under this arrangement you would be effectively outsourcing some of your data collection activities. Rather than waiting for patients to show up and then trying to take critical health measures you will have access to many of those same measurements already through our data services. This will increase your margin since most payer contracts pay some sort of fee for service.
      You will have the same fee but will not have to spend as much time taking the same basic measurements over and over. Additionally you can ask us to keep track of patient progress for any goals you have set for them and help them get paid in the process.
    </p>
    <p>
      Lastly, you can refer your patients for our services. If we have successfully contracted with their insurance we can help them to proactively manage their own health and possible make some money as well. If your group is happy with our services, you could think about making a financial investment with us and create a new revenue stream for the same number of patients. This can help you to get off the volume treadmill and allow you to focus on the issues of importance to you and your practice.
    </p>
  </div>
