    <p>
      For payers we offer the promise of better insight. Most providers are paid to treat conditions and the payers pay them after the services are rendered. This is called a retrospective payment system and it is the most common way that healthcare providers get paid.
    </p>
    <p>
      This creates great uncertainty for the payer since you never know which services will be rendered in any given period. Ajax Health will seek to reduce the risk of unknown health deterioration. By tracking the health of populations over time we can help payers to stay competitive with their
      rates and increase market share. We also offer wellness program administrative services. The American health profile is marked by significant increases in preventable health conditions. Poor diet and lack of exercise is causing healthcare costs to increase year after year. We will offer payments to patients
      who make progress towards reducing or eliminating their risk for preventable health conditions such as diabetes and obesity.
    </p>
    <p>
      We will provide contracted payers with information not found in claims or medical record audits - Data that even the most vertically integrated HMOs do not have access to. Namely what happened in between any interactions with the health care system. Patients who use this data to improve their health and reduce risk will be rewarded
      with payments under our targeted wellness programs.
    </p>
    <p>
      Our contracting strategy for our provider services is a mix of capitation and fee for service. Capitation revenue will be used to collect and provide access to population health data. We will also bill the appropriate Evaluation and Management CPT codes when specialists are needed to review individual patient data. 
      For our Wellness Program services we charge an administrative fee for enrolled members to offset the costs of administering any wellness programs a payer would like to offer their members.
    </p>
